 • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - The first case of coronavirus has been confirmed in the Western Cape. The Health Department reported that a 36-year-old man has tested positive for the virus. READ: Six new COVID-19 cases confirmed in SA He travelled to multiple countries including Germany, Austria, Switzerland and Turkey. The man returned to South Africa on 9 March. Western Cape premier Alan Winde and Provincial Minister of Health, Nomafrench Mbombo, will brief the media on the province's preparedness to deal with COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday